  "response": "In *Game of Thrones*, if you walked to Storm's End and knocked on the door asking who's in charge, the answer would depend on the specific timeline during the series or books. Here\u2019s a breakdown:\n\n1. **Early in the Series (Seasons 1-2 / Books 1-2)**:  \n   - **Renly Baratheon** would be in charge. He is the younger brother of Robert Baratheon and declares himself king, using Storm's End as one of his strongholds.\n\n2. **After Renly's Death (Seasons 2-4 / Books 2-3)**:  \n   - **Stannis Baratheon** takes control of Storm's End after Renly's assassination. He is the elder brother and claims the Iron Throne as Robert's rightful heir.\n\n3. **Later in the Series (Seasons 6-8 / Books 4-5 and beyond)**:  \n   - After Stannis\u2019s defeat and death, the castle would likely fall under the control of **House Umber** or another house loyal to the Lannisters or the Crown. By the end of the series, it\u2019s implied that **Gendry Baratheon**, legitimized as Robert\u2019s bastard son, becomes Lord of Storm's End.\n\nSo, the answer to your question would vary depending on when in the story this occurs. If you asked during a period of uncertainty or transition, the response might be cautious or even hostile, as Storm's End is a formidable fortress with a history of staunch loyalty to the Baratheons.",
